    <p>Amid the tu­mult of 2020, many turned to read­ing books for es­cape and so­lace.</p>
    <p>A survey by Toronto-based dig­i­tal read­ing com­pany Rakuten Kobo found that Kobo users in Sin­ga­pore spent more than 10,400 days read­ing this year – the equiv­a­lent of 28 years. They clocked 270 per cent more read­ing min­utes than last year, with May – dur­ing the cir­cuit breaker pe­riod – be­ing the month that peo­ple read the most.</p>
    <p>Here are The Sunday Times’ top 10 picks from 2020 to usher in a new year on a literary note.</p>

